menu "Vortex API test (vortex_api_test)"

    config VORTEX_API_TEST_STRICT_HW
        bool "Strict hardware checks (bench power + critical nets)"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, vortex_api_test fails if the Vortex V1 bench does not look
            electrically healthy: VM rail in range, TMC FAULT_n released, expected
            GPIO names registered, comms initialized, WS2812 diagnostics healthy, and
            ESP32 die temperature reads succeed.

            Expect nominal DC bus per docs/BENCH_MATRIX.md (e.g. 24 V). USB-only or
            unpowered boards should keep this disabled.

    config VORTEX_API_TEST_STRICT_SENSORS
        bool "Strict populated sensors (IMU, encoder, motor stack)"
        default n
        depends on VORTEX_API_TEST_STRICT_HW
        help
            Additionally require BNO08x and AS5047U stacks to enumerate, encoder angle
            read to succeed, and at least one motor controller device. Enable only when
            the full assembly is populated and wired.

endmenu
